race.comment: SHUTTER (3) returned from a six-month spell with a real eye-catcher last start, coming from last on the bend to be beaten just 1.6 lengths in a Class 3 over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Only carries 1kg more today after the claim in a far easier race. Very hard to beat out to this ideal distance. After five minor placings DWAYNE (1) finally cracked his maiden last time out when a comfortable winner over 1500m at Port Macquarie. Still has plenty of improvement to come at the third run back from a spell. The wide gate with a 4kg claimer to steer is the only knock. QUESTIONABLE (8) was back in form last start with a fast-finishing third over this distance at Quirindi. Lightly raced mare who gets all the favours from gate one and should be highly competitive. GHAZNAVI (5) stormed home at the end of 1450m at Muswellbrook recently. Rock hard fit and will be hard to hold out over this longer journey. BIG SHORT (2) strips fitter and is looking for the mile now.
